    "headline": "Climate Snapshot: A Year in Piemonte",
    "tagline": "A land that changes clothes four times a year — and always looks good in each.",
    "paragraphs": [
      "Piemonte lives in four full seasons — not the fake, two-season variety that flattens most of southern Europe. Here, winter actually bites, spring explodes, summer simmers, and autumn… steals the show.",
      "It's not the Italy of perpetual sunshine — it's the Italy of shifting light. Mist over vineyards in February. The sharp scent of cut hay in June. The gold rush of October leaves in the Langhe. Each month feels distinct, and that's part of its magic.",
      "Whether you crave Alpine winters or gentle vineyard warmth, this region gives you both — sometimes in the same weekend."
    ],
